Trump gave three nice things but very effectively used each nice thing to still go on the offensive (example: "she has lots of friends. She was the first to drop out in 2020, but now she is VP and the Democrat candidate while the others from 2020 are watching it on TV).

I cannot overstate how likable he was today. He def won some latrino votes.

posts.title: I'm in nursing school and my libtard classmate wrote a leadership essay about Kamala -- where can I find that screenshot of Joe Biden admitting that Kamala is a DEI hire, from the official whitehouse website before it got scrubbed?
posts.content:
Final Update, I found it and it's real!

  • https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/speeches-remarks/2024/05/29/remarks-by-president-biden-and-vice-president-harris-at-a-campaign-event-philadelphia-pa/#:~:text=To%20me%2C%20the%20values%20of,top%20with%20the%20Vice%20President.
  • "To me, the values of diversity, equality, inclusion are literally — and this is not kidding — the core strengths of America. That’s why I’m proud to have the most diverse administration in history that taps into the full talents of our country. And it starts at the top with the Vice President."

I'm in a group project and must convert her essay into a slideshow, and here is the relevant part of her essay:

Are leaders born, or are they trained?
There has been research to decide whether a person is born a leader or if a leader require training. Figuring out the answer to this question is important, because as the country grows there are more businesses that are set up. Those businesses require good leaders to continue to grow. In two months, the US has a crucial decision to make, who will be the president of the country, our new leader for four years. They have not publicized what characteristics the two candidates were born with, but there is information about the training and education both candidates received to aid with choosing our next leader. The two candidates have received different forms of training. Kamala Harris received training through college and then the Democratic Party, where she proved her leadership qualities and progressed in the Democratic Party. Donald Trump on the other hand, began his training at a youthful age at a military school and continued training in college. Then he went into the corporate world to received training and he showed the ability to run a business. He has been in the Republican Party for years but does not seem to be learning from their training. He is a businessperson and believes the country can be ran the same way as a business.

Here is the full essay if interested: https://pastebin.com/raw/tHmBZwXi

I absolutely remember seeing a viral post either here on TD or on twitter about an official whitehouse statement on DEI with Biden openly acknowledging that "DEI has a valuable place in my administration, starting with on the president ticket" or something to that effect?

I will send it to our group chat of 4 people (me and 3 women, probably all liberal) and take screenshots later today if it's funny or interesting. 😁
